  }, "\"like a spotless lake.\"")), mdx("p", null, "The enemy who attempted the mind-attack is instantly remorseful and feels a kind of warmth. Watching that scene, I was so distraught that I kept telling myself that he was actually a crazy person. That kind of personality comes from a world where the sun goes down and gaeva monsters come out and eat people."), mdx("p", null, "In reality, the idea of a teenage boy being kind in a harsh world and slicing up his enemies with all his heart is so unrealistic that it's almost kitschy and insane. It's a little bit like the ", mdx("a", {
    parentName: "p",
    "href": "https://m.post.naver.com/viewer/postView.naver?volumeNo=29284697&memberNo=5079266"
  }, "real vs. fake insanity meme"), " that's been going around a lot lately, where you keep seeing people on the real side of insanity."), mdx("p", null, "Problem-solving. This is a bit annoying to put in a post like this because it's so startup-y, but I'm just going to do it. If you work in a startup, you should not only watch EO, but also Nengdang Demon Blade."), mdx("p", null, "It's a very fast growth story with 100% opportunity in a tricky fight at every moment. The tricky enemies in the manga have pretty complex abilities. Like... It's not easy to figure out how to break them because they split up and you have to hit the main body,\nWhen I'm fighting, I'm constantly asking myself questions, testing hypotheses, and trying to figure out the enemy's behavior. This, coupled with arousal that matches the enemy's characteristics, allows me to defeat them."), mdx("p", null, "He's always empty when he delivers the final blow. He always emerges victorious with blood on his face and one broken joint.\nThere's a very detailed scene in the second Annie where she delivers a blow to an enemy with two broken knuckles and a lot of pain, and you can't help but cringe. It's like, \"This is going to really, really hurt.\"\nWhen you finally get past that and take down the enemy, it's the same feeling of exhilaration and ease that you get after beating hundreds of bosses in a Souls-like game, and it's also mind-blowing."), mdx("p", null, mdx("a", {
    parentName: "p",
